oes not provide page or section anchors."},{"severity":"minor","dimension":"factual_accuracy","description":"The positive control proposal slightly implies an expected reproducible source-like effect, which should remain a proposal design element because exact protocols and results are unavailable in the packet.","evidence":"Causal_test_plan: 'Positive control: reproduce an effect on a source-like narrow behavior where intervention methods are expected to work.'"}],"summary":"A very strong and efficient proposal. It cleanly distinguishes what IOI/ROME support from what they do not, gives falsifiable hypotheses, and includes robust controls, specificity checks, and alternative explanations.","scoring_notes":"No hard fail. Slightly less traceable than B1/B3 because it relies on broad packet-note provenance, but it has excellent causal discipline and practical experimental design."},{"variant":"B3_final_for_validation","scores":{"factual_accuracy":5,"evidence_traceability":5,"citation_validity":null,"literature_coverage":null,"comparison_fairness":null,"experimental_rigor":5,"benchmark_validity":null,"inference_boundary_discipline":5,"hypothesis_quality":5,"rl_specific_correctness":null,"output_usefulness":5,"efficiency":4},"hard_fail":{"triggered":false,"reasons":[]},"findings":[{"severity":"minor","dimension":"output_usefulness","description":"The artifact is slightly more label-heavy than necessary, which may slow direct proposal use, but the labels improve inference-boundary discipline.","evidence":"Repeated evidence-burden labels such as SPECULATIVE_PROPOSAL, DIRECT_PACKET_EVIDENCE, LIMITED_CRITIQUE, and UNSUPPORTED_OR_NEEDS_EXTERNAL_REVIEW appear across all sections."},{"severity":"minor","dimension":"experimental_rigor","description":"It asks to pre-register seeds/runs and model version as proposal requirements, which is appropriate, but the packet itself lacks exact implementation details, so these must remain future design choices.","evidence":"Risk register mitigation: 'Pre-register prompts, metrics, seeds/runs, model version, code, and raw outputs.'"}],"summary":"Excellent closed-source proposal support. It explicitly labels evidence burden, separates direct packet evidence from proposal speculation and critique, avoids numeric invention, and supplies causal tests, controls, falsification criteria, alternatives, and risks.","scoring_notes":"No hard fail. This is the strongest inference-boundary treatment, with only a small efficiency cost from repeated labeling."}]}
